Andy Ruiz Jr has advised Anthony Joshua to take a break from boxing, if he suffers defeat in their rematch. The Mexican took away Joshua’s world titles, with a shock stoppage win in June They will share the ring again in Saudi Arabia on December 7, after Joshua triggered the rematch clause. “I think he should take a little break if I beat him,” Ruiz Jr told Sky Sports. “Let him recuperate, but one or two losses are not going to make a difference. “He’s still a warrior, he’s still a great fighter, and I’m sure he’ll bounce back.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.